Yes, you can disable the default context menu on the whole component in React by attaching an event handler to the `onContextMenu` event and preventing the default behavior. By doing so, you can prevent the context menu from appearing when a user right-clicks on the component.

Here's an example of how you can achieve this:

```jsx
import React from 'react';

