```

In this example, the `handleContextMenu` function prevents the default behavior of the context menu when a user right-clicks on the component. As a result, the context menu will not appear, effectively disabling it for the whole component.

Keep in mind that disabling the context menu is a UX decision that may affect how users interact with your application. Make sure to consider the impact on user experience when choosing to disable the context menu.

